race.comment: MATRON SAMSING (1) resumed for the new yard off a narrow defeat and a win on the Ballarat and Pakenham synthetics and was slow off. She's sure to have come on from that and is proven second-up. Well placed to take this out. KING BLING (3) is ready to break through after a near miss in Maiden company. Was heavily bet off decent efforts in this grade. Will skip over to the speed and deserves another chance. BOSS SHELBY (4) got the job done by 3 lengths last time out over 1000m, finding the front after an awkward start. A decent chance holding that form.  APOLAKI (7) was having his first run for the Greg Connor team last start when he made steady ground beaten 1.3L. The former South Australian has the rail and deserves plenty of consideration as well.
